1→# StellarStage Carnival – Clean Architecture Blueprint
     2→
     3→_This document is a living, executable specification of how StellarStage Carnival’s JavaScript / TypeScript code-base is organised.  All code blocks are copy-paste ready for production and every design decision is mapped to a concrete implementation detail._
     4→
     5→---
     6→
     7→## 1. Layered Onion
     8→
     9→```mermaid
    10→graph LR
    11→    A[Presentation<br/>React + Three.js] --> B[Application<br/>GraphQL / WebSocket Gateway]
    12→    B --> C[Use-Cases<br/>Orchestrators]
    13→    C --> D[Domain<br/>Entities & Value Objects]
    14→    C --> E[Domain Services<br/>Factories, Strategies, State-Machines]
    15→    C --> F[Event Bus<br/>Observer Pattern]
    16→    C --> G[Port Adapters<br/>Ethereum, IPFS, Streaming]
    17→    G --> H[External Systems<br/>L1/L2, CDN, Storage]
    18→```
    19→
    20→* Nothing in `Domain` depends on outer layers.  
    21→* `Use-Cases` know only the `Domain` and well-defined `Ports`.  
    22→* `Adapters` implement the `Ports`, allowing for painless chain upgrades.
    23→
    24→---
    25→
    26→## 2. Domain Layer (Pure, No Side-Effects)
    27→
    28→### 2.1 Value Objects
    29→
    30→```ts
    31→// src/domain/value-objects/Address.ts
    32→export class Address {
    33→  constructor(private readonly value: string) {
    34→    if (!/^0x[a-fA-F0-9]{40}$/.test(value)) {
    35→      throw new Error(`Invalid Ethereum address ${value}`);
    36→    }
    37→  }
    38→  equals(other: Address): boolean {
    39→    return this.value.toLowerCase() === other.value.toLowerCase();
    40→  }
    41→  toString(): string {
    42→    return this.value;
    43→  }
    44→}
    45→```
    46→
    47→### 2.2 Entities
    48→
    49→```ts
    50→// src/domain/entities/Show.ts
    51→import { AggregateRoot } from '../shared/AggregateRoot';
    52→import { Address } from '../value-objects/Address';
    53→
    54→export interface ActProps {
    55→  id: string;
    56→  name: string;
    57→  performerAddr: Address;
    58→  startAt: Date;
    59→  endAt: Date;
    60→}
    61→
    62→export interface ShowProps {
    63→  id: string;
    64→  title: string;
    65→  owner: Address;
    66→  acts: ActProps[];
    67→}
    68→
    69→export class Show extends AggregateRoot<ShowProps> {
    70→  get id() { return this.props.id; }
    71→  get acts() { return this.props.acts; }
    72→
    73→  addAct(act: ActProps) {
    74→    if (this.props.acts.find(a => a.id === act.id)) {
    75→      throw new Error(`Act ${act.id} already exists`);
    76→    }
    77→    this.props.acts.push(act);
    78→    this.addDomainEvent({ type: 'ActAdded', payload: act });
    79→  }
    80→}
    81→```
    82→
    83→---
    84→
    85→## 3. Application Layer (Use-Cases)
    86→
    87→### 3.1 Port Definitions
    88→
    89→```ts
    90→// src/application/ports/blockchain/NftGateway.ts
    91→import { Pass } from '../../domain/entities/Pass';
    92→
    93→export interface NftGateway {
    94→  mintPass(pass: Pass, to: string): Promise<string>; // returns tx hash
    95→  upgradePass(tokenId: string, traits: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void>;
    96→}
    97→```
    98→
    99→### 3.2 Use-Case Service Example – MintShowPass
   100→
   101→```ts
   102→// src/application/use-cases/MintShowPass.ts
   103→import { ShowRepository } from '../ports/repositories/ShowRepository';
   104→import { PassFactory } from '../services/PassFactory';
   105→import { NftGateway } from '../ports/blockchain/NftGateway';
   106→import { EventBus } from '../ports/event/EventBus';
   107→
   108→export class MintShowPass {
   109→  constructor(
   110→    private readonly showRepo: ShowRepository,
   111→    private readonly passFactory: PassFactory,
   112→    private readonly nftGateway: NftGateway,
   113→    private readonly bus: EventBus,
   114→  ) {}
   115→
   116→  async execute(cmd: { showId: string; userWallet: string }) {
   117→    const show = await this.showRepo.byId(cmd.showId);
   118→    if (!show) throw new Error('Show not found');
   119→
   120→    const pass = this.passFactory.createForShow(show, cmd.userWallet);
   121→
   122→    const txHash = await this.nftGateway.mintPass(pass, cmd.userWallet);
   123→    await this.showRepo.savePass(pass);
   124→
   125→    this.bus.publish({ type: 'PassMinted', payload: { txHash, passId: pass.id } });
   126→    return { txHash, passId: pass.id };
   127→  }
   128→}
   129→```
   130→
   131→---
   132→
   133→## 4. Domain Services
   134→
   135→### 4.1 Factory Pattern – PassFactory
   136→
   137→```ts
   138→// src/application/services/PassFactory.ts
   139→import { ulid } from 'ulid';
   140→import { Pass } from '../../domain/entities/Pass';
   141→import { Show } from '../../domain/entities/Show';
   142→
   143→export class PassFactory {
   144→  createForShow(show: Show, ownerWallet: string): Pass {
   145→    return new Pass({
   146→      id: ulid(),
   147→      showId: show.id,
   148→      ownerWallet,
   149→      level: 1,
   150→      traits: this.defaultTraits(show),
   151→    });
   152→  }
   153→
   154→  private defaultTraits(show: Show) {
   155→    return {
   156→      theme: show.title.toLowerCase().includes('comedy') ? 'funny' : 'epic',
   157→      rarityScore: Math.random() * 100,
   158→    };
   159→  }
   160→}
   161→```
   162→
   163→---
   164→
   165→## 5. Infrastructure Layer
   166→
   167→### 5.1 Ethereum Adapter (uses ethers.js)
   168→
   169→```ts
   170→// src/infrastructure/blockchain/EthersNftGateway.ts
   171→import { ethers } from 'ethers';
   172→import { NftGateway } from '../../application/ports/blockchain/NftGateway';
   173→import abi from './StellarPass.json';
   174→
   175→export class EthersNftGateway implements NftGateway {
   176→  private contract: ethers.Contract;
   177→
   178→  constructor(
   179→    private readonly provider: ethers.providers.JsonRpcProvider,
   180→    private readonly signer: ethers.Signer,
   181→    contractAddress: string,
   182→  ) {
   183→    this.contract = new ethers.Contract(contractAddress, abi, signer);
   184→  }
   185→
   186→  async mintPass(pass, to) {
   187→    const tx = await this.contract.safeMint(to, pass.metadataUri);
   188→    await tx.wait(2);
   189→    return tx.hash;
   190→  }
   191→
   192→  async upgradePass(tokenId, traits) {
   193→    const tx = await this.contract.setTraits(tokenId, JSON.stringify(traits));
   194→    await tx.wait(1);
   195→  }
   196→}
   197→```
   198→
   199→### 5.2 Event Bus Adapter
   200→
   201→```ts
   202→// src/infrastructure/event/WebSocketEventBus.ts
   203→import WebSocket from 'ws';
   204→import { EventBus, DomainEvent } from '../../application/ports/event/EventBus';
   205→
   206→export class WebSocketEventBus implements EventBus {
   207→  private readonly wss = new WebSocket.Server({ noServer: true });
   208→  private readonly listeners: Set<(e: DomainEvent) => void> = new Set();
   209→
   210→  publish(event: DomainEvent): void {
   211→    const json = JSON.stringify(event);
   212→    this.listeners.forEach(cb => cb(event));
   213→    this.wss.clients.forEach(client => client.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN && client.send(json));
   214→  }
   215→
   216→  subscribe(cb: (e: DomainEvent) => void): void {
   217→    this.listeners.add(cb);
   218→  }
   219→}
   220→```
   221→
   222→---
   223→
   224→## 6. Reactive Pipeline (Observer → Strategy → State-Machine)
   225→
   226→```ts
   227→// src/application/services/ShowStateMachine.ts
   228→import { createMachine, interpret } from 'xstate';
   229→import { EventBus, DomainEvent } from '../ports/event/EventBus';
   230→
   231→export class ShowStateMachine {
   232→  private readonly service;
   233→
   234→  constructor(private bus: EventBus) {
   235→    const machine = createMachine({
   236→      id: 'show',
   237→      initial: 'scheduled',
   238→      states: {
   239→        scheduled: { on: { ActStarted: 'live' } },
   240→        live: { on: { ActEnded: 'break' } },
   241→        break: { on: { ActStarted: 'live', ShowEnded: 'ended' } },
   242→        ended: { type: 'final' },
   243→      },
   244→    });
   245→
   246→    this.service = interpret(machine).onTransition(state => {
   247→      bus.publish({ type: 'ShowStateChanged', payload: { state: state.value } });
   248→    });
   249→    this.bus.subscribe(this.onEvent.bind(this));
   250→  }
   251→
   252→  start() { this.service.start(); }
   253→
   254→  private onEvent(evt: DomainEvent) {
   255→    this.service.send(evt.type as any);
   256→  }
   257→}
   258→```
   259→
   260→---
   261→
   262→## 7. Proxy Smart Contracts (Upgrade-safe)
   263→
   264→```solidity
   265→// contracts/StellarPassProxy.sol (snippet)
   266→contract StellarPassProxy is ERC1967Proxy {
   267→    constructor(address _logic, bytes memory _data)
   268→        ERC1967Proxy(_logic, _data) {}
   269→}
   270→```
   271→
   272→_Key points_
   273→
   274→1. Implementation logic lives in `StellarPass.sol`.
   275→2. Proxy delegates calls, preserving storage layout for future upgrades.
   276→3. Royalties enforced via EIP-2981 in implementation contract.
   277→
   278→---
   279→
   280→## 8. Persistence & CQRS
   281→
   282→* Command side uses a fast Hot-Path DB (PostgreSQL + Prisma).
   283→* Query side is materialised into Apollo GraphQL subgraphs.  
   284→* Both are kept in sync via the Event Bus to ensure eventual consistency.
   285→
   286→---
   287→
   288→## 9. Observability & Error Handling
   289→
   290→```ts
   291→// src/infrastructure/logging/pinoLogger.ts
   292→import pino from 'pino';
   293→export const logger = pino({ level: process.env.LOG_LEVEL ?? 'info' });
   294→
   295→// Example usage
   296→try {
   297→  await nftGateway.mintPass(pass, wallet);
   298→} catch (err) {
   299→  logger.error({ err, passId: pass.id }, 'Failed to mint pass');
   300→  throw new MintPassError(pass.id, err);
   301→}
   302→```
   303→
   304→---
   305→
   306→## 10. Testing Strategy
   307→
   308→1. Domain & Use-Cases – pure unit tests (Jest).  
   309→2. Contract tests for Ports (pact-style mocks).  
   310→3. Solidity contracts – Foundry + Hardhat coverage > 95 %.  
   311→4. End-to-End – Playwright + Ganache snapshotting.
   312→
   313→```ts
   314→// tests/use-cases/mintShowPass.spec.ts
   315→describe('MintShowPass', () => {
   316→  it('mints and publishes event', async () => {
   317→    const result = await useCase.execute({ showId, userWallet });
   318→    expect(result.passId).toBeDefined();
   319→    expect(eventSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith(expect.objectContaining({ type: 'PassMinted' }));
   320→  });
   321→});
   322→```
   323→
   324→---
   325→
   326→## 11. Security Blueprint
   327→
   328→* All off-chain messages signed via EIP-712.  
   329→* On-chain re-entrancy guarded.  
   330→* Role-based access (`DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE`, `MINTER_ROLE`).  
   331→* Continuous audit pipeline with Slither + MythX.
   332→
   333→---
   334→
   335→## 12. Deployment Matrix
   336→
   337→| Env | Chain | Storage | Endpoint                  |
   338→|-----|-------|---------|---------------------------|
   339→| dev | Hardhat | local IPFS | http://localhost:4000 |
   340→| staging | Polygon Mumbai | Pinata | https://staging.api.stellar | 
   341→| prod | Ethereum Mainnet | Filecoin | https://api.stellar |
   342→
   343→---
   344→
   345→> The architecture is designed to remain chain-agnostic: swapping Ethereum for Solana is merely a matter of implementing the same Ports in a new Adapter without touching business rules.
   346→
   347→_This concludes the blueprint._

