1→```markdown
     2→# StellarStage Carnival – Smart-Contract Interaction Guide
     3→Interact with the on-chain backbone of the Carnival from a Node.js service, a React dApp, or even a serverless function. All snippets use TypeScript flavored JavaScript and `ethers@6.x`, but are easily portable to web3.js, viem, Foundry scripts, or Hardhat tasks.
     4→
     5→---
     6→
     7→## Table of Contents
     8→1. Prerequisites
     9→2. Contracts & ABIs
    10→3. Bootstrapping a Provider & Signer
    11→4. Read-Only Queries
    12→5. Stateful Transactions
    13→6. Event Subscriptions
    14→7. Error Handling Patterns
    15→8. Gas & Fee Optimisations
    16→9. Advanced: Meta-Tx & Permit2
    17→10. Reference Utilities
    18→
    19→---
    20→
    21→## 1. Prerequisites
    22→```bash
    23→npm i ethers@^6.10 dotenv@^16.4 zod@^3.22
    24→# For node < 20 add: npm i --save-dev @types/node
    25→```
    26→Create a `.env` file containing:
    27→```env
    28→RPC_URL=https://mainnet.infura.io/v3/<PROJECT_ID>
    29→PRIVATE_KEY=0xabc123...              # For backend/bot wallets
    30→CHAIN_ID=1                           # 1 Mainnet, 5 Goerli, 8453 Base, etc.
    31→```
    32→
    33→---
    34→
    35→## 2. Contracts & ABIs
    36→| Alias             | Proxy Address                                | Domain Entity | Upgrade Admin |
    37→|-------------------|----------------------------------------------|---------------|---------------|
    38→| ShowPassProxy     | `0x1cA5…BEEF`                                | `Pass`        | `0x7F0…135`   |
    39→| LootChestProxy    | `0xDeaD…CAFE`                                | `Loot`        | `0x7F0…135`   |
    40→| CarnivalGovernor  | `0xFabC…A11A`                                | Governance    | `–`           |
    41→| VotingEscrow      | `0xEscR…0LL`                                 | `Stake`       | `–`           |
    42→
    43→All production ABIs are collated under `@/contracts/abi/`. Example import:
    44→
    45→```ts
    46→import ShowPassABI from '@/contracts/abi/ShowPassProxy.json' assert { type: 'json' };
    47→```
    48→
    49→---
    50→
    51→## 3. Bootstrapping a Provider & Signer
    52→```ts
    53→// src/lib/blockchain.ts
    54→import { JsonRpcProvider, Wallet } from 'ethers';
    55→import { config } from 'dotenv';
    56→import { z } from 'zod';
    57→
    58→config();
    59→
    60→const EnvSchema = z.object({
    61→  RPC_URL: z.string().url(),
    62→  PRIVATE_KEY: z.string().regex(/^0x[a-fA-F0-9]{64}$/),
    63→  CHAIN_ID: z.coerce.number().positive()
    64→});
    65→
    66→const { RPC_URL, PRIVATE_KEY, CHAIN_ID } = EnvSchema.parse(process.env);
    67→
    68→export const provider = new JsonRpcProvider(RPC_URL, CHAIN_ID);
    69→
    70→// A signer is _only_ required for state-changing transactions.
    71→export const signer = new Wallet(PRIVATE_KEY, provider);
    72→```
    73→
    74→---
    75→
    76→## 4. Read-Only Queries
    77→```ts
    78→// src/queries/isPassUpgradable.ts
    79→import { Contract } from 'ethers';
    80→import { provider } from '@/lib/blockchain';
    81→import ShowPassABI from '@/contracts/abi/ShowPassProxy.json' assert { type: 'json' };
    82→
    83→const SHOW_PASS_ADDRESS = '0x1cA5…BEEF';
    84→
    85→/**
    86→ * Check whether a given tokenId can still evolve.
    87→ */
    88→export async function isPassUpgradable(tokenId: bigint): Promise<boolean> {
    89→  const contract = new Contract(SHOW_PASS_ADDRESS, ShowPassABI, provider);
    90→  try {
    91→    const level = await contract.currentLevel(tokenId);
    92→    const maxLevel = await contract.MAX_LEVEL();
    93→    return level < maxLevel;
    94→  } catch (error) {
    95→    console.error('Read error in isPassUpgradable ➜', error);
    96→    return false;
    97→  }
    98→}
    99→```
   100→
   101→---
   102→
   103→## 5. Stateful Transactions
   104→### 5.1 Mint a ShowPass
   105→```ts
   106→// src/tx/mintShowPass.ts
   107→import { Contract } from 'ethers';
   108→import { signer } from '@/lib/blockchain';
   109→import ShowPassABI from '@/contracts/abi/ShowPassProxy.json' assert { type: 'json' };
   110→
   111→const SHOW_PASS_ADDRESS = '0x1cA5…BEEF';
   112→
   113→/**
   114→ * Mints a new ShowPass for the connected wallet.
   115→ * @param tier 0 = GA, 1 = VIP, 2 = Ultra
   116→ * @param referralCode Optional bytes32 affiliate code
   117→ */
   118→export async function mintShowPass(tier: number, referralCode = '0x') {
   119→  const showPass = new Contract(SHOW_PASS_ADDRESS, ShowPassABI, signer);
   120→
   121→  // Optional: Estimate for better UX
   122→  const gas = await showPass.mint.estimateGas(signer.address, tier, referralCode);
   123→
   124→  const tx = await showPass.mint(signer.address, tier, referralCode, {
   125→    gasLimit: gas + (gas / 10n) // add 10% safety margin
   126→  });
   127→
   128→  console.info(`Mint submitted ➜ ${tx.hash}`);
   129→  const receipt = await tx.wait();
   130→  console.info(`Mint confirmed in block ${receipt.blockNumber}`);
   131→  return receipt;
   132→}
   133→```
   134→
   135→### 5.2 Stake Pass (Voting Escrow Pattern)
   136→```ts
   137→// src/tx/stakePass.ts
   138→import { Contract } from 'ethers';
   139→import { signer } from '@/lib/blockchain';
   140→import VotingEscrowABI from '@/contracts/abi/VotingEscrow.json' assert { type: 'json' };
   141→import ShowPassABI from '@/contracts/abi/ShowPassProxy.json' assert { type: 'json' };
   142→
   143→const ESCROW = '0xEscR…0LL';
   144→const SHOW_PASS = '0x1cA5…BEEF';
   145→
   146→export async function stakePass(tokenId: bigint, weeks: number) {
   147→  const escrow = new Contract(ESCROW, VotingEscrowABI, signer);
   148→  const pass   = new Contract(SHOW_PASS, ShowPassABI, signer);
   149→
   150→  // Approve once, stake many
   151→  const approved = await pass.isApprovedForAll(signer.address, ESCROW);
   152→  if (!approved) {
   153→    const approveTx = await pass.setApprovalForAll(ESCROW, true);
   154→    await approveTx.wait();
   155→  }
   156→
   157→  const lockUntil = BigInt(Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000) + weeks * 7 * 24 * 60 * 60);
   158→
   159→  const tx = await escrow.lock(tokenId, lockUntil);
   160→  console.info(`Staking tx ➜ ${tx.hash}`);
   161→  return tx.wait();
   162→}
   163→```
   164→
   165→### 5.3 Cast a Live Vote
   166→```ts
   167→// src/tx/castLiveVote.ts
   168→import { Contract } from 'ethers';
   169→import { signer } from '@/lib/blockchain';
   170→import GovernorABI from '@/contracts/abi/CarnivalGovernor.json' assert { type: 'json' };
   171→
   172→const GOVERNOR = '0xFabC…A11A';
   173→
   174→export async function castLiveVote(proposalId: bigint, support: 0 | 1 | 2) {
   175→  const governor = new Contract(GOVERNOR, GovernorABI, signer);
   176→
   177→  const params = await governor.proposalSnapshot(proposalId);
   178→  if (BigInt(Date.now() / 1000) < params.startTime) {
   179→    throw new Error('Voting has not started yet.');
   180→  }
   181→
   182→  const tx = await governor.castVote(proposalId, support);
   183→  console.info(`Vote tx ➜ ${tx.hash}`);
   184→  return tx.wait();
   185→}
   186→```
   187→
   188→---
   189→
   190→## 6. Event Subscriptions
   191→```ts
   192→// src/subscriptions/showPassEvents.ts
   193→import { Contract } from 'ethers';
   194→import { provider } from '@/lib/blockchain';
   195→import ShowPassABI from '@/contracts/abi/ShowPassProxy.json' assert { type: 'json' };
   196→
   197→const SHOW_PASS = '0x1cA5…BEEF';
   198→
   199→export function subscribeToPassEvolution(cb: (tokenId: bigint, level: number) => void) {
   200→  const pass = new Contract(SHOW_PASS, ShowPassABI, provider);
   201→  pass.on('LevelUp', (tokenId, level, event) => {
   202→    console.debug('Pass evolved:', { tokenId, level, tx: event.transactionHash });
   203→    cb(tokenId, Number(level));
   204→  });
   205→  return () => pass.removeAllListeners('LevelUp');
   206→}
   207→```
   208→
   209→---
   210→
   211→## 7. Error Handling Patterns
   212→1. Always wrap read calls inside `try/catch` to avoid crashing renders.
   213→2. Decode revert reasons for on-chain failures:
   214→```ts
   215→import { getRpcError } from 'ethers';
   216→
   217→try {
   218→  await contract.doSomething();
   219→} catch (e) {
   220→  const reason = getRpcError(e)?.info?.error?.message ?? 'Unknown error';
   221→  toast.error(`Tx failed: ${reason}`);
   222→}
   223→```
   224→3. Apply exponential back-off when polling confirmations in flaky networks.
   225→
   226→---
   227→
   228→## 8. Gas & Fee Optimisations
   229→• Prefer `staticCall` (aka call-static) to simulate transactions off-chain.  
   230→• Batch multiple mints with `multicall(aggregate)` via `CarnivalMulticaller`.  
   231→• Use EIP-1559 params: `maxFeePerGas`, `maxPriorityFeePerGas`.  
   232→• Monitor `baseFee` with `provider.getFeeData()` and queue non-urgent jobs.
   233→
   234→---
   235→
   236→## 9. Advanced: Meta-Tx & Permit2
   237→`ShowPassProxy` implements ERC-2771 recipient; you can pay gas on behalf of users.
   238→
   239→```ts
   240→import { signTypedData } from '@wagmi/core'; // or viem
   241→// …generate typedData object…
   242→const signature = await signTypedData({ domain, types, value });
   243→
   244→await carnivalForwarder.execute({
   245→  target: SHOW_PASS,
   246→  data: pass.interface.encodeFunctionData('levelUp', [tokenId, traitHash]),
   247→  signature
   248→});
   249→```
   250→
   251→---
   252→
   253→## 10. Reference Utilities
   254→```ts
   255→// src/utils/retry.ts
   256→export async function retry<T>(
   257→  fn: () => Promise<T>,
   258→  attempts = 3,
   259→  delayMs = 1_000
   260→): Promise<T> {
   261→  try {
   262→    return await fn();
   263→  } catch (err) {
   264→    if (attempts <= 1) throw err;
   265→    await new Promise(res => setTimeout(res, delayMs));
   266→    return retry(fn, attempts - 1, delayMs * 2);
   267→  }
   268→}
   269→```
   270→
   271→---
   272→
   273→Happy building, and see you on the Stellar Stage! 🚀
   274→```

